WEBVTT

00:04.881 --> 00:06.048
GARRETT:
Well, that's what you said.

00:06.049 --> 00:07.814
I did not say
"when hell freezes over."

00:07.817 --> 00:08.750
What then?

00:08.753 --> 00:10.519
I said I will make my decision

00:10.522 --> 00:12.656
when the mayor gets his head
out of his ass.

00:12.657 --> 00:13.855
Sorry, wrong cliché.

00:13.859 --> 00:15.057
Oh, cut it out.
And his head's

00:15.060 --> 00:16.393
not out of his ass?

00:16.393 --> 00:17.859
Is it partly out?

00:17.862 --> 00:18.894
Do you have a progress report?

00:18.896 --> 00:20.297
I'll make it simple
for you!

00:20.298 --> 00:23.733
When the mayor asks me to re-up,
himself, in person...

00:23.734 --> 00:24.833
And what's with all
the qualifiers?

00:24.835 --> 00:25.702
That's two qualifiers!

00:25.702 --> 00:27.268
Two!
And the peas cannot touch

00:27.271 --> 00:28.571
the mashed potatoes.

00:28.574 --> 00:29.739
I serve at the pleasure
of the mayor.

00:29.740 --> 00:32.942
All I ask is that he ask me
to re-up!

00:32.945 --> 00:34.677
He's trying to schedule
a signing ceremony.

00:34.679 --> 00:35.679
That's not the same thing.

00:35.680 --> 00:37.380
With you and yours
and the brass

00:37.381 --> 00:39.381
and press in formation.
That is not the same thing!

00:39.383 --> 00:41.549
It's <i> the</i> thing!
Did Mrs. Moore hire the hall

00:41.551 --> 00:44.185
and the caterers <i> before</i>
you asked her to marry you?

00:44.188 --> 00:45.720
It's not the same thing.

00:45.723 --> 00:47.490
Well, it's damn close.
Same principle.

00:48.759 --> 00:52.262
Some requests,

00:52.264 --> 00:54.463
some decisions,

00:54.466 --> 00:58.167
deserve to have
protocol respected.

00:58.170 --> 01:01.570
Deserve to have it honored.

01:01.573 --> 01:02.706
Or what?

01:02.707 --> 01:05.242
Or what? Or what?
What do you mean, "Or what?"

01:05.242 --> 01:07.010
How long you gonna
let this go on?

01:07.012 --> 01:09.045
As long as it takes
the mayor and you

01:09.046 --> 01:10.579
to accept the fact
that I will

01:10.581 --> 01:12.248
only do this one way.

01:12.251 --> 01:12.915
Your way.

01:12.918 --> 01:15.150
The right way.

01:15.152 --> 01:18.587
I serve at the pleasure
of the mayor, and you serve

01:18.590 --> 01:19.823
at the pleasure
of the commissioner.

01:19.825 --> 01:21.156
Am I right?

01:21.158 --> 01:22.224
Yes, sir.

01:22.227 --> 01:23.460
Then act like it.

01:24.495 --> 01:26.028
If you're so eager
to make this happen,

01:26.031 --> 01:29.132
make it happen the way
your boss wants it to happen.

01:33.138 --> 01:35.771
(jazz piano playing)

01:35.774 --> 01:39.408
(laughing)

01:39.411 --> 01:40.676
What's so funny?

01:40.679 --> 01:42.078
Nothing.

01:42.079 --> 01:43.479
It's my frisée salad,
isn't it?

01:43.481 --> 01:44.747
(chuckles)

01:44.750 --> 01:46.549
I look like a giant wimp
right now.

01:46.551 --> 01:48.218
You're picturing me in a dress.

01:48.219 --> 01:50.219
No, no, it's nothing like that.

01:50.222 --> 01:52.289
It's just been a long time
since I've done this

01:52.290 --> 01:56.293
and an even longer time
since I've enjoyed it.

01:56.295 --> 01:57.926
(phone ringing)

01:58.930 --> 02:01.197
(sighs)
Anthony.

02:01.198 --> 02:02.399
Uh-oh.

02:02.400 --> 02:04.266
Who's Anthony?

02:05.037 --> 02:06.736
Sorry. Hello?

02:06.737 --> 02:08.237
Hey, Erin. It's me, Anthony.

02:08.240 --> 02:09.872
Yes, Anthony, I know.

02:09.875 --> 02:12.141
I have caller I.D.,
just like everyone else

02:12.144 --> 02:14.210
in the Western Hemisphere.
(chuckles)

02:14.211 --> 02:15.412
We got a problem.
You should get down here.

02:15.413 --> 02:18.147
I just texted you the address.

02:18.150 --> 02:20.783
You're texting the wrong number.
I'm not catching tonight.

02:20.786 --> 02:22.686
Erin, listen,

02:22.687 --> 02:24.920
trust me,
you need to get down here.

02:24.923 --> 02:26.923
We got a cop shot and killed.

02:27.759 --> 02:29.959
Oh, no. I'm on my way.

02:29.961 --> 02:33.195
Erin, wait. Wait.

02:33.198 --> 02:34.364
I'm really sorry, but...

02:34.365 --> 02:35.698
You're certain
that wasn't just

02:35.700 --> 02:38.901
one of your girlfriends calling
to get you out of here, right?

02:38.903 --> 02:40.804
A police officer's been killed.

02:40.805 --> 02:43.105
I'm sorry.

02:45.000 --> 02:51.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:52.783 --> 02:54.683
Excuse me.

02:54.686 --> 02:55.918
Detective Reagan.

02:55.920 --> 02:57.486
Yes.

02:57.489 --> 02:58.722
Sergeant Rutkowski.

02:58.723 --> 03:00.223
I'm here on instructions
from Lieutenant Gormley.

03:00.224 --> 03:01.457
I'm supposed to give you this.

03:02.426 --> 03:05.127
What exactly is
Lieutenant Gormley gifting me?

03:05.129 --> 03:06.596
A missing cop.

03:06.598 --> 03:08.431
Missing how?

03:08.432 --> 03:10.734
Officer Kenneth Nelson
missed roll call

03:10.735 --> 03:11.901
about four hours ago.

03:11.902 --> 03:13.269
DANNY:
And the CO declared him AWOL?

03:13.271 --> 03:14.637
Yeah. That's right.

03:14.639 --> 03:16.139
Okay. Who's this?

03:16.140 --> 03:18.408
Officer Abrams.
I'm Kenny's partner.

03:18.409 --> 03:19.675
Yeah, I brought him along.

03:19.677 --> 03:21.243
Thought you might want
to pick his brain.

03:21.246 --> 03:23.112
So?

03:23.115 --> 03:24.013
Kenny's a good cop.

03:24.014 --> 03:25.281
Have you heard from him?

03:25.283 --> 03:26.316
No, I haven't.

03:26.318 --> 03:27.449
That's not so good.

03:27.451 --> 03:28.518
Kenny's been having
a tough time lately.

03:28.520 --> 03:30.954
I'm not sure
if that has anything to do

03:30.955 --> 03:32.756
with him not showing today,
but...

03:32.757 --> 03:35.424
I wanted to put it out there.
I'm...

03:35.426 --> 03:38.328
not exactly sure what it is
you're putting out there.

03:38.329 --> 03:39.995
Officer Nelson's son
passed away

03:39.997 --> 03:41.396
a couple years back.

03:41.400 --> 03:42.865
Leukemia.
Oh.

03:42.867 --> 03:44.734
Well, I'm sorry.

03:44.735 --> 03:47.336
Kenny's boy was just seven
years old when he lost him.

03:47.338 --> 03:50.372
Needless to say, the guy's
never been the same since.

03:50.375 --> 03:52.040
Okay.

03:52.043 --> 03:53.810
I'll get on it.

03:58.682 --> 04:00.015
I called you back five times!

04:00.018 --> 04:01.784
Every time,
straight to voicemail.

04:01.787 --> 04:04.721
I know. I'm sorry. I was on
the phone with the office,

04:04.723 --> 04:06.122
and then
my cell died in the tunnel.

04:06.123 --> 04:07.257
Where's the body? This way?

04:07.259 --> 04:08.390
Listen, we got to talk.

04:08.393 --> 04:09.692
Yeah, I think I got
everything on the way.

04:09.693 --> 04:10.794
Listen...

04:10.795 --> 04:12.694
Officer Donald Gibson.
12 years on the job.

04:12.697 --> 04:16.199
Was shot approximately 9:17 p.m.
in a drug deal gone bad.

04:16.201 --> 04:18.100
Yeah, but listen...
Where's his partner?

04:18.103 --> 04:20.670
I heard he got a glimpse of
the shooter when he was fleeing.

04:20.672 --> 04:21.805
Yeah, he did.

04:21.807 --> 04:22.939
He-He's right over there.
Great.

04:22.940 --> 04:24.374
Erin, listen...
Let's start there.

04:24.375 --> 04:26.675
Erin! Hang on.

04:26.677 --> 04:28.778
Anthony, I just want
to get the description

04:28.779 --> 04:30.146
while it's fresh in his mind.

04:30.148 --> 04:31.747
We already got the shooter.

04:31.750 --> 04:33.649
What? Well, that's great.

04:33.651 --> 04:35.985
Yeah. The partner put
the description over the air

04:35.987 --> 04:37.353
right after the shooting.

04:37.355 --> 04:39.122
RMP picked him up
about ten minutes ago.

04:39.124 --> 04:40.824
But we have a problem.

04:40.826 --> 04:43.393
The shooter's name
is Adrian Cooke.

04:43.394 --> 04:44.661
Adrian Cooke?

04:44.663 --> 04:45.862
Yes.

04:56.574 --> 04:58.274
Anthony,
what are you telling me?

04:58.276 --> 05:00.877
Nothing.
I-I'm just saying what I said.

05:02.146 --> 05:04.613
You mean to say
I'm responsible for this?

05:12.456 --> 05:16.456
